page.title: 05Housing in Wembley
page.content:
Most of the houses in our area are either semi-detached or terraced houses and have gardens both back and front.Usually the corner houses are the biggest and have the biggest gardens.
Many of the houses were built in the 1930's as the {Underground Railway spread out from{Central London. {} They are built of brick and have a red tile roof and pebble-dashing on the walls.Most of them have two storeys.
There are very few tall blocks of flats in our area but several 3 or 4 storey blocks.
